productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Seed Sowing Now Simple And Easy With Kraft Seeds 1) Prepare Soil Before Sowing The Seeds, By Mixing Agropeat Or Manure With Soil (30:70), It Will Help In Germination Of Seeds, If You Are Not Able To Find Good Quality Agropeat Or Manure, You May Also Use The Available Soil. Just Make Sure That The Soil Is Clean From Any Weed Or Insect. 2) Open The Seed Packet On A White Sheet Of Paper As While Opening The Seeds Might Fall, Which Are Not Visible To Naked Eyes. While Opening The Packet The Seed Might Fall On The White Sheet And You Might Save The Seeds Which Otherwise Would Have Lost. 3) After Preparing The Soil, Dip The Seeds In The Said Soil, Half (0.5) Inch Deep In It. Thereafter Water It By Only Sprinkling Water Through A Sprinkler Or Manual Hands, Do Not Use Pipe Or A Mug To Water For The First Week, As The Force Of Water Might Break Or Splash Out The Seed. 4) Germination May Take Place 10-15 Days, Depending Upon Different Varieties. Once The Seeds Grow In To Seedlings, Say Around 3 Inches, Then You May Transplant The Seedlings To Various Pots Or Desired Areas. 5) Time To Time Check That The Growing Plant Is Not Infected By Any Weed/Pest/ Or Insect, And If You Find Any Such Thing On The Leaves Or In Soil Then You May Spray (Chloropyriphos / Cypermethrin) On It. 6) Use Kraft Seeds - Organic Manure Once In 15 Days For The Growth Of The Flower/Plant. Happy Seedings! From Kraft Seeds!

Growing 3 to 4 feet tall the lightly ruffled buds cover most of the stem opening in slow succession from bottom to top. Gladiolus requires a sunny well drained bed . productBaseInfoV1.title: Kraft Seeds Brinjal Round Seed
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Seed Sowing Now Simple And Easy With Kraft Seeds 1) Prepare Soil Before Sowing The Seeds, By Mixing Agropeat Or Manure With Soil (30:70), It Will Help In Germination Of Seeds, If You Are Not Able To Find Good Quality Agropeat Or Manure, You May Also Use The Available Soil. Just Make Sure That The Soil Is Clean From Any Weed Or Insect. 2) Open The Seed Packet On A White Sheet Of Paper As While Opening The Seeds Might Fall, Which Are Not Visible To Naked Eyes. While Opening The Packet The Seed Might Fall On The White Sheet And You Might Save The Seeds Which Otherwise Would Have Lost. 3) After Preparing The Soil, Dip The Seeds In The Said Soil, Half (0.5) Inch Deep In It. Thereafter Water It By Only Sprinkling Water Through A Sprinkler Or Manual Hands, Do Not Use Pipe Or A Mug To Water For The First Week, As The Force Of Water Might Break Or Splash Out The Seed. 4) Germination May Take Place 10-15 Days, Depending Upon Different Varieties. Once The Seeds Grow In To Seedlings, Say Around 3 Inches, Then You May Transplant The Seedlings To Various Pots Or Desired Areas. 5) Time To Time Check That The Growing Plant Is Not Infected By Any Weed/Pest/ Or Insect, And If You Find Any Such Thing On The Leaves Or In Soil Then You May Spray (Chloropyriphos / Cypermethrin) On It. 6) Use Kraft Seeds - Organic Manure Once In 15 Days For The Growth Of The Flower/Plant. Happy Seedings! From Kraft Seeds!

productBaseInfoV1.title: EZBond 1 - Pronged Hook
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: EZBond Power HookMaterials: ABS, PVCMade in TaiwanPower Hook can hold weight up to 2.3 kgsPATENTSUS Patent No. 10380023Japan Patent No. 600874Taiwan Patent No. 194524Korea Patent No. 0320919China Patent No. ZL012104441.8PCT Patent No. 01932092.7EZBond Power-Hook serves as a best solution, wherever nails can't be pierced on to the wall/surface, which might damage the surface or make it worse looking. EZBond Power-Hook is a patented product which can stick to walls with a help of an accessory sticker with the product or without the sticker on smooth non-porous surfaces like glass, smooth tiles, mirror, marble or granite surfaces. Its specialty - it can hold up to 2.3 Kgs with much ease. It can be used multiple times. It is made of thin film. It sticks to surface based on surface tension. So, it sticks very well. It is waterproof and is impervious to a wide range of cleaning products. It can be quickly and easily removed for cleaning and then reattached with no loss of grip.Instructions1. Thoroughly clean and dry the glass/wall/surface.2. Carefully peel the protective backing label from the film on the back of the hook. Do it with patience to avoid any stretch or damage to the film.3. Press the hook firmly onto the glass/wall/surface to which it is to be fixed and working from the inside to the outside. Smooth the film onto the surface and make sure that all wrinkles and air pockets / bubbles have been pressed out.4. Pull on the hook to ensure that it is securely fastened to the surface. If the hook moves or detaches, clean the surface and follow step 3 again.5. Now you can hang on whatever you like. It has got numerous applications. productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Prepare Soil Mixed With Organic Manure Or Compost Before Sowing The Seeds*After All Frost And Check Soil Is Clean From Any Weed Or Insect*Open The Seed Packet On A White Sheet Of Paper As While Opening The Seeds Might Fall, Which Are Not Visible To Naked Eyes*After Preparing The Soil, Sprinkle The Seeds Over The Soil Cover The Seeds With Little Soil Or Press With Gentle Hand*While Watering, Care Needs To Be Taken To Only Sprinkling Water Through A Sprinkler Or Manually Using Your Hands*Do Not Use Pipe Or A Mug To Water For The First Week, As The Force Of Water Might Damage The Seed Germination Process*Germination May Take Place 10-18 Days, Depending Upon Different Varieties*For Herbs/Small Seeds Variety Special Care Needs To Be Taken Cover The Sowing Area With Transparent Polythene In Evening For Fast Germination*All Flowers, Tomatoes, Chilli, Peppers, Brinjal Etc All Needs To Be Transplant Once The Plant Is 3-4 Inch*All Varieties Require Very Less Water, And Need Sunlight Min 2-3 Hours Daily For Winter Variety 1-2 Hours Sun Is Fine For Germination Process*Happy Gardening*Team Seedscare-Rama Beej Bhandar
